storyInfo: Those around her have moved on. It's time she made her own choice.

attributes.content: What are you doing in Jessica's room, Vanilla?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Franka!
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: Ah, I'm helping her clean up.
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: ...I guess our princess isn't going to be around the ship a lot, now that she's off at the frontier.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Yeah, Jessica and I talked it over. I'm cleaning up her room so I can mail her her stuff.
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: Need any help?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: No, I borrowed a few gadgets from Engineering. I can handle this on my own.
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: Guess you're not that little girl who used to walk into automatic doors anymore.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Teehee.
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: Franka.
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: Hm?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Do you think Jessica was wrong?
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: She told you to ask me that, didn't she?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: ...Yeah.
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: Still worrying what other people think, even after making a decision like that?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I can't tell if she's actually grown up or not.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: ...I really admire her.
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: She's willing to leave everything behind...
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: Heh, no need to rush to her defense.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Jessica has her fair share of problems, but she knows what she's doing.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I've known from the start that she's not the kind of person I need to be worrying about.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I just didn't expect her to make a decision so soon.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Soon?
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: Yeah. She's barely twenty. Practically a baby.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: She has plenty of time ahead of her.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Hm...
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: But it's not a bad thing.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Sure beats being someone who could never make a choice at all.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I'm sorry!
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: What?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I've been thinking about my future too, but I couldn't come to a decision...
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: Oh. Sorry, I wasn't talking about you.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: You're pretty young too, aren't you?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I was taking about...
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: ...Who was I talking about again?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I'll go look for a Messenger to make the delivery.
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: Go ahead.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: It's me.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: A mission? I'll be there right away.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Find something to pass the time between missions.
Should be easy enough, she thinks.
As she prepares to leave the room, she hears a voice that makes her stop in her tracks.
I understand.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: No, my plans haven't changed.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: I still want to form my own security company.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Mr. Cliff wants to speak to me?
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Understood. I'll return to HQ tomorrow.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Franka?
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Normally, she would go over to her partner and make a face at her.
Maybe even play a practical joke or two, if she was in a good mood.
But todayâ€”
Yes, she's aware.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: ...I know.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: I'll discuss it with her.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: ...What am I running away from?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Franka?
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Good timing. I'm going back to HQ.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Something happen?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Like I told you before, I'm planning to talk to Mr. Cliff.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: So you've made up your mind?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Yes. Seeing Jessica's courage made me feel like I should be braver, too.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: It's a fine line between courage and recklessness. Sure you're ready to face the 'Clip'?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I don't mind coming with, for moral support.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: ...No, I've got to get used to it.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: You don't have a deceptive bone in your body. You don't stand a chance against that sly old man.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: You're in a bad mood today, aren't you?
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: And what does that have to do with anything?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I've been around you long enough to pick up a thing or two about reading people.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Looks like the teacher's pet has grown up, too.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Franka.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Hm?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: We need to talk when I get back.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: You serious?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Am I ever not?
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: I'll be gone for a month or so. See you.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Okay, fine, maybe I'm not in the best mood.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Report.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: The intel was good. The bandits have taken the workers hostage and are holed up in the depot.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: They have equipment and numbers, but there are plenty of holes in their defenses.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: I'm sending you a map of the buildings and sentry positions.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Received.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Whew...
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: What is it?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I was worried that you and Liskarm would be wasted at a pharmaceutical company.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: But now I can see that what you do hasn't really changed.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: You could've taken it easy if you applied to Logistics or HR, you know.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: No way. Field Operator pays well. Better than at Blacksteel, anyway.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: And I've always wanted to try my hand at this.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Being on the frontlines is no game.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Which is why I applied to join a mission with you two leading the charge.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Can't wait to study the veterans in action.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: There isn't much worth learning on the battlefield.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: It's not a place to spend your life.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Doesn't matter, knowledge is money, no matter where it comes from.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: I want to make money while I can, so I'll have the freedom to do what I want.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: And what's that?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Well, I haven't decided yet.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: But I will.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Must be nice to be young.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: You're not that much older than me.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Says the girl who's been my junior at both Blacksteel and Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: What, would you like a massage? A back rub?
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: No thanks.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I'm sending over the operation plan now.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Wow, that was quick!
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: And really detailed!
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: I hope you've learned to respect your elders.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I've always respected you, oh venerable one.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Team A will pin the enemy from the front, while Team B rescues the hostages.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Do you have enough people to pin them down?
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Based on earlier intel, their leader is very cautious and may choose to flee if we deploy too many.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: We don't want to have to chase them through the hills.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Still, this few people in Team A...
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Oh, did no one ever tell you this?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: 'Keep an eye on Franka when Liskarm's away. Don't let her do anything reckless.'
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Er... just to be clear...
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Yeah, I know. You didn't hear that from Liskarm herself.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Our honor student would have said it to my face.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: But I guess we've been partners for too long.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: So long that even Rhodes Island likes to stick us together.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Isn't that a good thing?
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Why would you think that?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Isn't it comforting to be with someone you can trust?
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: You have a tendency to seek thrills in battle, leading you to take dangerous actions.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: While Liskarm is cautious and tries to stop you.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: You often argue, but are the perfect partners to complete any missions assigned to you.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: That's what they say about you two back at Blacksteel, anyway.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Well, they're not wrong.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: The two of us have gotten used to it, is all.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: The Vulpo sighs.
Most new Blacksteel members choose a standard-issue weapon when they join.
She picked a shortsword for self-defense, but the rapier remained her main weapon.
As time went on, people started to believe that she only used the rapier.
In fact, she is skilled with the shortsword too.
But it's been so long that even she herself has almost forgotten.
Let's do this quickly.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Franka pinned the enemy down while the rest of us rescued the hostages.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Then I turned around to see that they had surrounded her.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: What?!
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: My heart was practically in my throat at that point.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: They weren't very well-equipped, but they had the advantage of numbers.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: And they all wanted a piece of her after realizing they'd been fooled.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: But Franka just stood there like there was nothing to worry about.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: I thought maybe Liskarm's absence had made her go over the edge...
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: But thenâ€”
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Then?
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: This is an exclusive scoop. You didn't expect to hear it for free, did you?
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Almond makes a money sign with her hand and smiles slyly.
...Alright, alright!
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: Ouch!
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: You shouldn't be trying to make money off other people's stories.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: This is just an efficient use of resources!
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Oh, Liskarm! You're back.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Mm-hm.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Were you talking about Franka?
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Yup.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: I want to hear it too.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Fine, fine, this one's on the house.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Thanks!
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: Man, I'm starting to feel guilty.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Anyway!
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Franka was in the middle of the fray, while I was on the tower after getting the hostages out.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: We didn't plan any strict timing. She shouldn't have known where I was.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: But I saw her wink directly at me.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: With her gaze, she drew my attention to a teetering building on the other side.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Right next to the bandits.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: I got the message instantly.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: She didn't show herself just for the thrill of it. She lured them there on purpose.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: She even predicted that I would show up right where I did!
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: It's no superpower. She simply expected that enough time would have elapsed for you or some other team member to show up.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: What if we got delayed though?
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Then she might have rendezvoused with you, or she might have had a Plan B.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: If I were in her shoes, I might have set up explosives in the building.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Come to think of it, she did ask me for some explosives...
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Anyway, there was something different about Franka on this mission.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Calm, reliable... not to say she's not normally reliable, butâ€”
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: Where is she now?
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: She shut herself in her room after she got back.
attributes.name: Vanilla

attributes.content: Yeah... I wanted to celebrate with her.
attributes.name: Almond

attributes.content: ...I'll go find her.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Almond is probably running her mouth off right about now.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Bah, it's none of my business.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Her mother's letter lies on the table.
She regularly sends her mother money and answers every question she has. She loves her.
But there are two questions that she always evades.
How long do you plan on risking your life as a mercenary?
When are you coming home?
They are, in fact, the same question.
She knows her mother is asking out of love, but these two questions mean more to her than anyone can imagine.
The Vulpo turns on the old record player that she got from Croissant.
Then, she sinks herself into the soft bed, as though trying to fall into an abyss where no one knows her.
She has never considered herself unprepared for the future.
She believes she is enjoying every second of the present.
But she felt a sense of loss when Jessica decided to go to the frontier. When Liskarm decided to form her own security company.
It isn't about uncertainty. She knows exactly where she should be heading.
It'sâ€”
She knows who this polite and rhythmic knocking belongs to.
She knows I'm in here, and where I left the spare key.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Underneath the flower pot by the door.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Then, she'll open it up without hesitation.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Maybe I should change where I hide the key.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: This isn't like you, Franka.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: And what would be?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: ...Anything but this.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Are you free right now, Teacher's Pet?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I wouldn't have come looking for you if I wasn't.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: We haven't sparred in a while, have we?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: So you just laid out all your ideals. As usual.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I don't know any other way.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Well, I guess it suits you better than trying to sweet talk him.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: So how did it go?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Not great. Mr. Cliff is not fond of my choice.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: But he did say he wouldn't mind having a far-off partner.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: There's no such thing as a real partnership between security companies. Once you leave Blacksteel, you're no friend of them.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I know.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: The two of them walk towards opposite ends of the training ground.
You heard about it from Laura.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Yes.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: I know why you want to spar all of a sudden.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: So we'll spar to your heart's content today.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Aren't you getting a little carried away, Teacher's Pet?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I mean exactly what I said.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Sword and shield meet with a loud clang.
I also saw a few friends that I've kept in touch with since my trainee days.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Many of them are willing to come with me.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: So you went back for a class reunion?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Not exactly, we just had a few chats.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: They all asked about you.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Me?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: You always call me 'honor student' or 'teacher's pet,' but you were the one who was always at the top of the class.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Being an honor student isn't exactly a good thing for a warrior.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I disliked you from the moment I laid eyes on you.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I know.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: I remember the first time we faced off in a simulation.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: What did I say?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: You said, 'Let's see if the teacher's pet is so perfect in a real fight.'
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: That's when it all started.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: You sure can hold a grudge.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: You could always stop calling me that.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: No way.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: They know each other's moves well. The sound of weapons clanging against one another fills the room.
I mean, why would someone who's neither a wannabe warlord nor an arms dealer become a mercenary?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I still wonder that.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I don't need to hear that from someone who says she became one for the thrill of it.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Looks like our teacher's pet has learned a retort or two.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I learned from the best.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: I saw the letter when I stepped into the room.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: You haven't been back for years.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: I don't know what to say when I see her.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I thought you got along well enough with your mother.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: More than well enough. I love her, and she loves me.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: She encouraged me to do what I wanted, and never forced me to do anything I didn't.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: She spoiled me into the woman I am today.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I can see that.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: There are a lot of mercenaries like me, at least in terms of personality.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: But very few like you, who seek out danger rather than avoid it.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: It took me a long time to realize why.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: You could do that because you can afford to live a carefree life.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Yeah, you should see the pictures of me from when I was little.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Not to gloat, but you've never seen a more pampered princess.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Er, thanks, but no thanks.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Well, I'm not sure I have any of those around anyway.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I'm sure Mom kept them, though.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: But the more I enjoy what I have now, the more afraid I am of seeing her.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I shouldn't have left her.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I should have stayed with her, started a little shop. All I needed was enough income to make a living.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: But I couldn't resist my longing for... all this.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Franka points at her sword, then turns around to look at the spacious training ground.
She was worried about me when I was a freelance mercenary.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: So she sent me off to Blacksteel training camp with a smile.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: But I know she cried as soon as I was out of sight.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Are you afraid you won't be able to leave once you go see her?
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: I'm afraid I wouldn't be able to stop myself from arguing with her.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Even though we love each other so much.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: ...I thought you were just in a bad mood.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Apparently you're in a very bad mood.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: All these years, and I've never heard you talk so much.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Yeah, our thing was always you talk, and I laugh at you.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Your condition isn't getting worse, is it?
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Don't worry, I'm fine.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: It's not any better, but it's not worse either.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I've gotten used to touching the hard bits when I take a shower.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Maybe I've gone crazy though. Who knows?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Not everyone needs a grand dream or ideal.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Feeling myself grow in battle, playing pranks on the people around meâ€”
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: That's enough for me.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: From Blacksteel to Rhodes Island, I think I've been more happy than not.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: And I thought I could go on like this.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Until you and Jessica both made your choices.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Then I realized I really, really couldn't.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: So I had to ask myselfâ€”
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Where do I go from here?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Everything came so easily to you, Franka. Everyone admired you.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Myself included.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: ...Wait, really? You?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Yes, me.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: The one who pulled me back on our first mission?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: It didn't stop me from thinking you took way too many risks.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: For a long time, I didn't quite understand why I partnered with you. But now I've started to.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: I could never tell what you were thinking, but I always wanted to know...
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: What kind of outlook on life did someone like you have, someone who is so different from me?
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Maybe I instinctively realized that I could learn a lot from you.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: I don't remember you learning anything from me.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I've learned plenty. Combat skills, witty retorts... maybe a positive mindset?
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Or maybe it would be more accurate to say you forced me to pick them up on my own, to keep up with you.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Take that mission you went on with Laura...
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: You're Franka.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: You might look like you need someone to back you up, but you really don't.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: All you needed was someone to give you a little push.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Are you... breaking up with me?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I just wanted you to let you knowâ€”
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: You don't need to worry about me.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Well, you've definitely learned how to get on my nerves, at least.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I learned from the best.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: The Thermite Blade pops out of her hand, drawing a dangerous arc as it flies through the air, while the Flash Shield slips from the Vouivre's hand and falls to the ground.
A draw, as usual.
But Franka did not pick up her weapon while making fun of Liskarm, as she normally did.
She simply stands there, lost in thought.
Liskarm waits.
Finally, Franka breaks the silence.
You said you needed to talk with me.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: You want to invite me to join your new security company, don't you?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Correct.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Well, I'm not going.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Not yet.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Okay.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Liskarm picks up the Thermite Blade, and Franka the Flash Shield, and they both toss them to the other.
My condition has mostly stabilized.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: I want to take a long vacation. Go home and spend some time with my mom.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Maybe have a big fight with her.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: And then... I think I'm going to go on a long trip.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: A long-term field mission, maybe, to some place far away.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: You might even have your company up and running by the time I get back.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Then when the time comes, I'll invite you to hang out.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Don't get ahead of yourself.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Oh?
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: You're the one who followed me to Rhodes Island, remember?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Maybe someday, after I leave this place, I'll go shamelessly hang out at your office without asking.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Sorry, but you know me. Rules are more important than relationships.
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Well, then I guess I'll hang out outside your office and put up a sign with all your most embarrassing secrets.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: ...How the hell did I end up getting to know someone like you?
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: You know, that's a great question. My condolences.
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: So what's for lunch?
attributes.name: Franka

attributes.content: Who's buying?

attributes.content: Fine, me. Just for today.
